{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/technical/how-to-install-multiple-python-versions/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Yajana Rao"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6fb25cbe-5d47-531c-88b0-c8b45d59b5de","excerpt":"For Mac OS Add the following in the shell script  List versions using Install another python version using command NOTE:\nIn case if you see any issue whileâ€¦","html":"<h2>For Mac OS</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">brew update\nbrew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> pyenv</code></pre></div>\n<p>Add the following in the shell script <code class=\"language-text\">~/.bash_profile</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">eval</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>pyenv init -<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">'PATH=$(pyenv root)/shims:$PATH'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> ~/.zshrc</code></pre></div>\n<p>List versions using</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">pyenv versions</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install another python version using command</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">pyenv <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token number\">3.6</span>.9</code></pre></div>\n<p>NOTE:\nIn case if you see any issue while installing the version checkout the following issue:\n<a href=\"https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/issues/1737\">https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/issues/1737</a></p>\n<p>The solution would be:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">CFLAGS</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"-I<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix openssl<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/include -I<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix <span class=\"token function\">bzip2</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/include -I<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix readline<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/include -I<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>xcrun --show-sdk-path<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/usr/include\"</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">LDFLAGS</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"-L<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix openssl<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/lib -L<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix readline<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/lib -L<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix zlib<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/lib -L<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>brew --prefix <span class=\"token function\">bzip2</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/lib\"</span> pyenv <span class=\"token function\">install</span> --patch <span class=\"token number\">3.6</span>.9 <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -sSL https://github.com/python/cpython/commit/8ea6353.patch<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>?full_index<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>To uninstall any version use the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">pyenv uninstall <span class=\"token number\">3.6</span>.0</code></pre></div>\n<p>To set specific python version in command line:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">pyenv <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">local</span> <span class=\"token number\">3.6</span>.9</code></pre></div>\n<p>The virtual environment can be created using the following command now:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">python3 -m venv venv</code></pre></div>\n<p>References:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/manage-multiple-python-versions-and-virtual-environments-venv-pyenv-pyvenv-a29fb00c296f/\">https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/manage-multiple-python-versions-and-virtual-environments-venv-pyenv-pyvenv-a29fb00c296f/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv\">https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://opensource.com/article/20/4/pyenv\">https://opensource.com/article/20/4/pyenv</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to install multiple python versions","date":null,"description":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/technical/how-to-install-multiple-python-versions/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/2020-08-15-python-concepts/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Python tutorial"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/2021-07-13-using-react-native-why-did-you-render/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use why did you render in react native"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["1205699325","1246554614","2841359383","3336116537"]}